When adding a new project, Jira should select the "Default Permission Scheme" by default instead of the first one that is listed alphabetically. Be consistent with the rest of the options in the project creation dialog.

See JSP-34380 for details backing up this issue.

A very minor change, where there are repeated references to _ManagerFactory.getMailQueue()_, I would like to provide an alternate implementation, which would be neatly addressed IF the following method were in place and used.  Otherwise I have to essentially duplicate most of the code, which I would like to avoid

{code:type=java}
protected MailQueue getMailQueue()
{
  return ManagerFactory.getMailQueue()
}
{code}

I'm developing a plugin, but need be able to modify the recipientList in order to filter some users out.  A simple setter is just what I need.

    /**
     * Used in testing only
     *
     * @return recipientList   the set of recipients to recieve this email notification
     */
    public Set setRecipientList(Set recipientList)
    {
        this.recipientList = recipientList;
    }

The addition of this method would remove the need for a code customization.

Minor point, could you remove the 'Used in testing only' text, I'd hate for these methods to go away!

Thanks,
andy

